.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::DerivationPath \- Path for BIP32 key derivation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::DerivationPath;
\&
\&        my $derivation_path = Bitcoin::Crypto::DerivationPath\->from_string("m/1/2\*(Aq/3");
\&
\&        say $derivation_path\->private;
\&        say $_ for @{$derivation_path\->path};
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a helper object which represents the key derivation path parsed from
the \f(CW\*(C`m\*(C'\fR notation. It is returned by "get_path_info" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Util.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
